25/10/2005
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Police have arrested three men suspected of plotting terrorist attacks on unspecified targets, authorities announced Monday (24 October). Two of the men hold Swedish and Turkish citizenship, respectively, but originally come from the former Yugoslavia. The third man is a Bosnian citizen. Police discovered a video recording apparently meant to be circulated after a suicide bombing. Security around embassies and headquarters of international organisations has been tightened.
In other news Monday, the Muslim Commission for Missing Persons reported that a new mass grave has been discovered in the village of Snagovo, 50km north of Srebrenica. Forensic experts expect to find the remains of victims of the 1995 Srebrenica massacre. (AFP, UPI, BBC - 24/10/05) 
